t><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=883.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaching yourself a language</span><hr size=1> Yes you could.  How?<br><br>Well you can teach someone 1 point better in a language then yourself.  So say you have 5 points in language.  You can teach someone to 6 points in that language.  Then they can teach you another 2 points to raise your skill to 7.  And visa versa.  So how it works?  Goes back and forth.  You can teach someone 1 point better in a langauge then your skill.  <br><br>This is how people learn Dragon and Combine and other dead languages.  <br><br>Happy Learning <p>Xinnem SwifthandsHalf Elf Rogue of Firiona Vie"Rogues do it best from behind"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 6:38:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=883.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Also, you don't ..</span><hr size=1> .. need an initial point.  You can select the language even if you don't know it and boot-strap yourself up from zero.  However, both your characters would need to be at least level 19 -- for FV only, languages cap at 5*(level + 1) with a 100 maximum.  On other servers, there is no per-level cap.  Also, for FV only, you have to zone after each skill-up (one skill-up per zone per hour).<br><br>Basically, being a polyglot is a lot harder on FV and also much more of a usefull accomplishment.  The only effect of speaking odd languages on other servers is to annoy your guildmates, most of whom likely don't speak anything but common -- it was also a nice way to find out which of the casters were &quot;first wave&quot; and which were twinks.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 330<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 10:07:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=883.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Also, you don't ..</span><hr size=1> So the way to learn it (fastest) is zone bounce.<br><br>Get both of your chars next to a zone line that is a &quot;fast zone&quot; preferably.<br><br>Switch OFF group in chat options, switch on group speak.<br>At this point we assume both have a skill of 1.<br><br>Now spam from A until you get a &quot;Your language skills have improved&quot; on B, now spam B until you get the same message on A.<br><br>Zone both and repeat.<br><br>This way is boring as hell but you can go from 1 point to master in about 1.5 hours.<br><br>Hugs<br><br>Intra<br><br>Master in:<br>Erudite<br>Human<br>Dwarven<br>Halfling<br>Gnome<br>Tier'Dal<br>Combine<br>Troll<br>Ogre<br>Iksar<br>Elvish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/